content.problemStatement:
Consider the following C code that initializes a 2D array representing temperatures recorded over 3 days in 3 cities and prints specific values.

What will be the output of this code?

```c
#include

int main() {
    // Declare and initialize a 2D array with temperatures (in °C) for 3 cities over 3 days
    int temps[3][3] = {
        {30, 32, 31},  // City 1
        {28, 29, 27},  // City 2
        {35, 36, 34}   // City 3
    };

    // Print temperatures of Day 1 for all cities
    printf("%d %d %d\n", temps[0][0], temps[1][0], temps[2][0]);

    // Print temperatures of Day 2 for all cities
    printf("%d %d %d\n", temps[0][1], temps[1][1], temps[2][1]);

    // Print temperatures of Day 3 for all cities
    printf("%d %d %d\n", temps[0][2], temps[1][2], temps[2][2]);

    return 0;
}
```

